# Core Services 2 (TNVS) PHP Deployment

This project has been converted from static HTML/CSS/JS to PHP so that
it can run under a PHP engine (e.g. XAMPP). The conversion includes:

- All frontend `.html` pages renamed to `.php` and wrapped with PHP tags.
- CSS and JavaScript assets converted to PHP scripts that send the correct
  `Content-Type` header.
- Links and script references updated to point at the new `.php` filenames.
- Markdown and text documentation files are now `.php` scripts that serve
  plain text.

## Getting started with XAMPP

1. Copy the entire project directory into your XAMPP `htdocs` folder, for
   example `C:\xampp\htdocs\BPM TNVS`.
2. Start Apache and MySQL via the XAMPP control panel.
3. Open a browser and visit `http://localhost/<folder>/index.php` to view the
   login page.
4. To create the database, visit `http://localhost/<folder>/db.php` or import
   the supplied `database.sql` schema using phpMyAdmin (accessible at
   `http://localhost/phpmyadmin`).
5. Adjust `db.php` credentials if you have a password on the `root` user.

## Notes

- Server-side logic can now be added inside `<?php ... ?>` blocks in any file.
- Static assets are still cached normally by browsers; their PHP wrappers just
  send headers and echo the original content.
- If you maintain the project in version control, consider excluding the
  `database.sql` file or renaming back to `.md` for documentation.

Happy coding!
